gomodel:SYNGO_2315  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3A: \"A punctate and discrete CapZ signal was found in the spines of CA1 pyramidal and dentate granule cells (Fig. 3A, N = 4 cells each from four mice from three independent experiments for CA1 apical, CA1 basal and dentate apical dendrites).\"\nFig. 3C. \"CapZ beta 2 was often detected at the postsynaptic density (arrows) and\nwas also found in the extrasynaptic plasma membrane and cytosol (arrowheads) of dendritic spines\". Experimental description: Fig. 3. \"Distribution and localization of CapZ in the hippocampus in vivo. (A) The CapZ i.r. (purple) in spines was examined in the brain sections of Thy1-mGFP (membrane-bound GFP; green) mice.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2315" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

